1. General Provisions.
   This User Agreement was originally drafted in Russian. The English version is provided solely for the convenience of Users. In the event of any contradictions or discrepancies between versions, the original Russian version shall have exclusive legal force.

Project name: Luna
Project type: Public Discord bot
Project owner: YunoSL
Contact information:
Github: https://github.com/YunoSL
Email: [help.lunabot@gmail.com](mailto:help.lunabot@gmail.com)
Discord: yuno_sl

By using Luna, you agree to these Terms of Use. If you do not agree — do not use the service.

2. Definitions:

2.1 Luna — a software product (bot) for the Discord platform that provides functionality to users. The full list of functions is available via the /help command in the Discord interface. Hereinafter — Luna.

2.2 User — an end user of Discord using the service.

2.3 Prohibited Content — It is forbidden to post, distribute, or provide access to Content that is illegal, malicious, threatening, defamatory, violates privacy, or that we, at our sole discretion, consider unacceptable. Prohibited Content includes, but is not limited to:
Sexual content: Pornography, explicit sexual materials, content related to sexual exploitation, as well as any materials depicting minors in a sexualized context.
Extremely violent and shocking content: Realistic depictions or descriptions of violence, cruelty, torture, murder, bodily harm, as well as images of corpses, dismembered bodies, or other consequences of violent acts in shocking detail.
Abuse of people or animals: Materials depicting or promoting physical or psychological abuse, humiliation, torture, or suffering inflicted on people or animals.
Hate content: Materials that promote violence or discrimination against individuals or groups based on race, ethnicity, religion, disability, gender, age, sexual orientation, or other characteristics.
Content violating human rights: Threats of violence, cyberbullying, harassment, invasion of privacy, and distribution of personal information without consent (doxxing).
We reserve the right, at our discretion, to remove any Content that violates these Terms and to take action against accounts that post such Content, including contacting Discord to request their blocking. Any content that violates Discord Terms of Use or Discord Community Guidelines is also considered Prohibited Content for the purposes of this Agreement.

2.4 User Content — any images, files, text descriptions, or other data voluntarily uploaded by the User to the Service (Luna) using the functionality of custom banners or other commands that provide for file uploads.

2.5 Custom banner — a graphic image uploaded by the User and temporarily or permanently stored by the Service for display in the user’s profile on a specific Discord server in accordance with Luna functionality.

3. Rules of Use:

3.1 When using Luna, the User is prohibited from:
1 — Using the bot functionality for unlawful or illegal actions,
2 — Using the bot for spam, phishing, and similar activities, violating Discord Terms of Use (https://discord.com/terms),
3 — Using the bot to distribute prohibited content,
4 — Any actions aimed at disrupting the bot’s operation: DDoS attacks, exploitation of vulnerabilities, and similar actions,
5 — Uploading, publishing, or transmitting through banner functionality any Content that falls under the definition of Prohibited Content (clause 2.3). The User bears sole responsibility for all images and data uploaded to the Service.

3.2 In case of violation of the rules of use, the Owner has the right to suspend or completely terminate access to the Service for a specific User or an entire server (guild) at their discretion, without mandatory prior notice.

3.3 Only users who have reached the minimum age required to use the Discord platform may use the service.

4. Service Provision:

4.1 The service is provided “as is,” without warranties. The Developer is not responsible for direct or indirect losses such as: loss of data inside the bot (database data, etc.), termination of the bot’s operation, loss of statistics, or losses resulting from the actions of the user or third parties.

4.2 The Developer also does not guarantee uninterrupted operation of the service and/or that it will meet expectations.

5. Data Collection and Use:

5.1 Luna has the right to collect user data necessary to provide functionality, such as: user IDs, server IDs, message IDs, user or server avatars, user nicknames, as well as other data required for specific commands and bot features. More details are available in the Official Privacy Policy:
Googledocs: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1tsoodfPLsBFTJe3UPCD88R-5NAhu0h8iLhOH_aubkHY/edit?usp=sharing
Github: https://github.com/YunoSL/Luna-terms./blob/main/TermsofUse

5.2Storage of User Content. User-uploaded banners are stored in the Service databases until they are manually deleted by the User through bot functionality, automatically replaced with a new banner, or until the Service is removed from a specific server. The Developer is not responsible for backups or guaranteed preservation of uploaded images.

6. Changes to the Terms of Use (ToU):

6.1 The Project Owner reserves the right to change the terms without notifying the user. The updated version takes effect upon publication. Continued use of the bot after the changes take effect means acceptance of them.

7. Rights to Luna:

7.1 All rights to the source code belong to the owner. The User receives a limited license to use the service.
7.2 Some graphic elements may be obtained from public sources and are used under the principle of fair use. In case of claims from rights holders, please contact using the details provided in Section 1.
7.3 Rights to User Content. Luna does not claim ownership of images uploaded by Users. All rights to original images remain with their lawful owners.
7.4 License to use content. By uploading an image to Luna, the User grants the Project Owner a free, non-exclusive license to store, copy (solely for backup creation or content delivery optimization), and publicly display the image in the Discord interface strictly within the operation of the Luna Service. The license remains valid until the User deletes this content from the Service.

8. Notice and Takedown:

8.1 If you are a rights holder or an authorized representative and believe that any content available through Luna violates your copyright or related rights, or contains Prohibited Content, please immediately contact us using the contacts in Section 1.

8.2 To speed up request processing, please provide:
A precise description of the content that violates rights.
Your contact information (email, Discord).
Proof of your rights to the object (or a statement that you act on behalf of the rights holder).

8.3 The Project Owner undertakes to review the complaint within a reasonable time and, if the claims are justified, remove the relevant content and take action against the violator in accordance with clause 3.2.

